,"1130":"1130","1170":"1170","1205":"1205","1303":"1303","1158":"1158","1200":"1200","December 1205":"December 1205","Withington, Lancashire, England":"Withington, Lancashire, England","Hulme, Lancashire, England":"Hulme, Lancashire, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Blacon, Chester, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hulme","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Holm   and of   Home   3 and 4."],"variants":[{"name":"Hume","meanings":["Scottish (Lowlands) and northern English: variant of   Hulme  , with loss of <i>l</i> before the bilabial consonant /m/, as in the vocabulary word <i>calm</i>. See   Holm   and   Home  .","Scottish: habitational name either from the barony of Home or from Hume (or Home) in Berwickshire, from which the barony took its name. The placename derives from Old English <i>hōum</i>, dative plural form of <i>hōh</i> ‘heel, spur of land’.","History: A family of this name (see 2 above) have held the Earldom of Home since 1605."]},{"name":"Holm","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Lars, Anders, Thor, Holger, Nels, Nils, Sven, Helmer, Lennart, Niels, Vibeke.","English, Scottish, German, and Scandinavian: topographic name for someone who lived on an island, in particular a piece of slightly raised land lying in a fen or partly surrounded by streams, from Middle English, Middle Low German <i>holm</i>, Old Norse <i>holmr</i>, or else a habitational name from a place called with this element. The Swedish name is often ornamental.","English: topographic name for someone who lived where holly grew, from Middle English <i>holm</i>, a divergent development of Old English <i>hole(g)n</i> ‘holly (tree)’; or, especially in southern England, a habitational name from any of the places such as East and West Holme (Dorset) or Holne (Devon). Compare   Hollis  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Hulme was born in 1154, in Hulme, Lancashire, England, his father, John Hulme, was 25 and his mother, Ormus Davenport, was 23. He married Mrs John de Hulme. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in December 1205, in his hometown, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1154–December 1205":"1154–detsember 1205","1154–1205":"1154–1205","1158–1200":"1158–1200","1175–1275":"1175–1275","–1303":"–1303","1130–1170":"1130–1170","1132–Female":"1132–Surnud","about 1150":"umbes 1150","after 1170":"pärast 1170","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1275":"1275","1175":"1175","1130":"1130","1170":"1170","1205":"1205","1303":"1303","1158":"1158","1200":"1200","December 1205":"detsember 1205","Withington, Lancashire, England":"Withington, Lancashire, England","Hulme, Lancashire, England":"Hulme, Lancashire, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Blacon, Chester, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1154–December 1205":"1154–joulukuu 1205","1154–1205":"1154–1205","1158–1200":"1158–1200","1175–1275":"1175–1275","–1303":"–1303","1130–1170":"1130–1170","1132–Female":"1132–Kuollut","about 1150":"noin 1150","after 1170":"1170 jälkeen","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1275":"1275","1175":"1175","1130":"1130","1170":"1170","1205":"1205","1303":"1303","1158":"1158","1200":"1200","December 1205":"joulukuu 1205","Withington, Lancashire, England":"Withington, Lancashire, England","Hulme, Lancashire, England":"Hulme, Lancashire, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Blacon, Chester, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1154–December 1205":"1154–décembre 1205","1154–1205":"1154–1205","1158–1200":"1158–1200","1175–1275":"1175–1275","–1303":"–1303","1130–1170":"1130–1170","1132–Female":"1132–Décédée","about 1150":"environ 1150","after 1170":"après 1170","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1275":"1275","1175":"1175